text: Val-du-Faby is a commune of 562 people (in the year 2017). It is in the region Occitanie in the Aude department in the south of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2019 and consists of the former communes of Fa and Rouvenac.Arrêté préfectoral 5 December 2018 == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Aude
title: Val-du-Faby
